Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), pandoc
Standards-Version: 4.6.0

Package: canlogger
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         can-utils,
         zstd,
         python3,
         rclone,
         bash (>= 4)
Description: CAN bus logger with session detection and cloud upload
 Captures candump output from can0 into time-bucketed, zstd-compressed segments
 with session detection (silence ends a session, traffic starts a new one) and
 ships finished segments to a configurable rclone remote.
 .
 The canlogger service is enabled automatically on install. The canlog-upload
 timer is installed but NOT enabled, because rclone needs configuring with the
 cloud destination first. See /usr/share/doc/canlogger/README.md for setup.
